        </div>
        <div class="cs-rich__steps cs-rich__steps--architecture">
          <div class="cs-rich__step">
            <div class="cs-rich__step-icon">
              <FadersHorizontalIcon size={22} weight="regular" aria-hidden="true" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="cs-rich__step-title">Strategic Orchestration</h3>
            <p class="cs-rich__step-desc">The Architect defines the project's unique needs, identifying where overrides to the core system are required. Using an AI-native editor, the Architect directs the system to plan structural changes based on high-level logic rather than manual pixel-pushing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-rich__step">
            <div class="cs-rich__step-icon">
              <PaletteIcon size={22} weight="regular" aria-hidden="true" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="cs-rich__step-title">Storybook Theming</h3>
            <p class="cs-rich__step-desc">Project-specific overrides are applied and tested directly in Storybook. This live sandbox allows the architect to validate how custom token values interact with existing components in real-time, ensuring the design works in a browser-native environment before it’s finalized.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-rich__step">
            <div class="cs-rich__step-icon">
              <StackSimpleIcon size={22} weight="regular" aria-hidden="true" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="cs-rich__step-title">Style Dictionary Core</h3>
            <p class="cs-rich__step-desc">Validated overrides are pushed to the Style Dictionary. This centralizes the project's logic into a platform-agnostic JSON layer, which then automatically compiles the correct variables for CSS, React, and mobile platforms—acting as the "Single Source of Truth."</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-rich__step">
            <div class="cs-rich__step-icon">
              <ArrowsClockwiseIcon size={22} weight="regular" aria-hidden="true" />
            </div>
            <h3 class="cs-rich__step-title">Bi-Directional Synchronization</h3>
            <p class="cs-rich__step-desc">The system ensures zero drift between intent and reality. While Figma remains a flexible entry point for mockups, it is no longer a bottleneck; since system rules live in component metadata, any generative AI can assemble production code directly. The loop then uses Bridge protocols to push code-first changes back to Figma, keeping the design file a living, accurate mirror of the architect’s decisions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

